UI/UX AUDIT FINDINGS & REMEDIATION PLAN
========================================
Generated: 2026-03-11
Auditor: Claude Opus 4.6
Status: IN PROGRESS

TABLE OF CONTENTS
1. Executive Summary
2. Quality Scores by Phase
3. Systemic Gaps Analysis
4. Phase 1-2 Remediation (Priority 1)
5. Cross-Phase Systemic Fixes (Priority 2)
6. World-Class Polish (Priority 3)
7. Implementation Order

═══════════════════════════════════════════
1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
═══════════════════════════════════════════

TOTAL FILES AUDITED: 65+ screen/page files, 78+ widget files, 212 total .dart files
TOTAL SCREENS: 42 pages across 9 feature packages
RESEARCH DOCS REVIEWED: 6 research .doc files + app-structure/README.md (2905 lines)

KEY FINDING: Phase 3-5 screens (8.1/10 avg) now EXCEED Phase 1-2 screens (6.4/10 avg)
after systematic upgrades applied to typography, shadows, haptics, animations, and touch targets.

Phase 1-2 needs the SAME treatment to reach parity, plus cross-phase systemic features
(shimmer loading, pull-to-refresh, stagger animations, responsive breakpoints) to reach
world-class (9.5+/10) quality.

